Jump to ContentHomeGuidesRecipesAPI ReferenceChangelogAPI ReferenceMoon (Dark Mode)Sun (Light Mode)HomeGuidesRecipesAPI ReferenceChangelogGetting Printable LabelsSearchCTRL-KAllGuidesRecipesReferenceChangelogStart typing to search‚Ä¶JUMP TOCTRL-/Sendle APIWelcome to the Sendle APIGetting Your API KeySendle's Sandbox ServerAuthenticating API RequestsParcel Weight and VolumeFirst Mile OptionsOrder States and FlowIdempotency KeysIdempotent EndpointsUsing Idempotency KeysDashboard Billing CSVPre-filled Send Parcel FormCommon API IssuesEndpointsTestingBasic API TestgetQuoting and OrderingGet productsgetGet a quote (deprecated)getCreate an orderpostView an OrdergetGetting Printable LabelsCancel an OrderdeleteShipping manifestsCreate shipping manifestpostGet all shipping manifestsgetGet status of shipping manifestgetGet orders on shipping manifestgetDownload shipping manifestgetReturnsReturn an orderpostView a return ordergetTrackingTrack a ParcelgetPublic Tracking PagePowered by¬†JUMP TOCTRL-/Sendle APIWelcome to the Sendle APIGetting Your API KeySendle's Sandbox ServerAuthenticating API RequestsParcel Weight and VolumeFirst Mile OptionsOrder States and FlowIdempotency KeysIdempotent EndpointsUsing Idempotency KeysDashboard Billing CSVPre-filled Send Parcel FormCommon API IssuesEndpointsTestingBasic API TestgetQuoting and OrderingGet productsgetGet a quote (deprecated)getCreate an orderpostView an OrdergetGetting Printable LabelsCancel an OrderdeleteShipping manifestsCreate shipping manifestpostGet all shipping manifestsgetGet status of shipping manifestgetGet orders on shipping manifestgetDownload shipping manifestgetReturnsReturn an orderpostView a return ordergetTrackingTrack a ParcelgetPublic Tracking PagePowered by¬†Getting Printable LabelsThe label is the piece of paper or sticker that you put on your parcel.It lets the driver know that it's a Sendle parcel and where it should go.We have two different PDF label options to choose from:

A cropped label, that's the perfect size already.A full-sized a4 (Australian) or letter (U.S.)sheet with a label on it.Our cropped label files have the physical size embedded.But some printing programs don't respect that and try to fill the whole page instead, and the labels end up much bigger than they should be.Using the full sheet makes sure they can be printed at the right size with a home printer.Generally you should let merchants choose which size to download and use, since which one they prefer will depend on their setup.Make sure that they're also only available when authenticated ‚Äì the labels contain a lot of personal information!Label Layouts
Our labels are laid out in specific ways to comply with the requirements of our delivery partners.Because of this, the layout of the labels we supply may change any time.We recommend supplying the labels as-is for shippers to print and not post-processing them ‚Äì¬†even rotating the label can degrade the quality of barcodes/text and make it more likely for packages to be lost during their journey.Trying to extract details from the labels or pull barcodes from them is also fragile and may break when we need to update the layout of the label.QR Code for drop off orders in Australia
Drop off orders originating from Australia, within 25km of an eligible Print In-Store service location will include a QR code version of the label.The label will available as a png format, as part of the label response.See more about QR code label in the Changelog and help centre article for Print In-Store service.Downloading a Label
When creating an order or viewing an order, you'll get an entry that looks like this:
